# Plan: Add PulseBoard Channel Plugin

## Context

OpenClaw supports pluggable messaging channels via the `openclaw/plugin-sdk/*` API. Each bundled channel plugin lives in `extensions/<id>/` and must implement a `ChannelPlugin` via `createChatChannelPlugin`, expose entry points via `defineChannelPluginEntry` / `defineSetupPluginEntry`, and carry a `package.json` + `openclaw.plugin.json` manifest.

The task creates a self-contained, stub-level `pulseboard` channel plugin under `extensions/pulseboard/` without modifying any existing file.

---

## Critical Design Note: `getChatChannelMeta` vs. Inline Meta

The task requirements mention using `getChatChannelMeta` from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/core`. However, that function only works for channel IDs registered in `CHAT_CHANNEL_ORDER` inside `src/channels/ids.ts` (telegram, whatsapp, discord, irc, etc.). "pulseboard" is not in that list, and we are not allowed to modify existing files.

**Pattern to follow:** `extensions/matrix/src/channel.ts` (Matrix is also a non-core extension) constructs its meta as a plain inline object:
```typescript
const meta = {
  id: "matrix",
  label: "Matrix",
  selectionLabel: "Matrix (plugin)",
  docsPath: "/channels/matrix",
  ...
};
```
`pulseboard/src/channel.ts` must do the same. `getChatChannelMeta` will NOT be imported or called.

---

## Reference Files (read-only)

| Purpose | File |
|---|---|
| IRC entry point pattern | `extensions/irc/index.ts` |
| IRC setup entry | `extensions/irc/setup-entry.ts` |
| IRC plugin manifest | `extensions/irc/openclaw.plugin.json` |
| IRC package metadata | `extensions/irc/package.json` |
| IRC channel plugin builder | `extensions/irc/src/channel.ts` |
| IRC runtime store | `extensions/irc/src/runtime.ts` |
| Nostr runtime store (simpler) | `extensions/nostr/src/runtime.ts` |
| Matrix inline meta pattern | `extensions/matrix/src/channel.ts` (lines 92-101) |
| `createChatChannelPlugin` | `src/plugin-sdk/core.ts` (line 536) |
| `ChannelOutboundAdapter` type | `src/channels/plugins/types.adapters.ts` (line 175) |
| `OutboundDeliveryResult` type | `src/infra/outbound/deliver.ts` (line 53) |
| `createPluginRuntimeStore` | `src/plugin-sdk/runtime-store.ts` |

---

## Files to Create (7 total, all in `extensions/pulseboard/`)

### 1. `extensions/pulseboard/package.json`

```json
{
  "name": "@openclaw/pulseboard",
  "version": "2026.4.1-beta.1",
  "description": "OpenClaw PulseBoard channel plugin",
  "type": "module",
  "devDependencies": {
    "openclaw": "workspace:*"
  },
  "peerDependencies": {
    "openclaw": ">=2026.4.1-beta.1"
  },
  "peerDependenciesMeta": {
    "openclaw": {
      "optional": true
    }
  },
  "openclaw": {
    "extensions": ["./index.ts"],
    "setupEntry": "./setup-entry.ts",
    "channel": {
      "id": "pulseboard",
      "label": "PulseBoard",
      "selectionLabel": "PulseBoard (Bulletin)",
      "docsPath": "/channels/pulseboard",
      "blurb": "Connect to PulseBoard bulletin messaging."
    }
  }
}
```

Key points:
- No runtime `dependencies` (stub, no third-party libs needed)
- `openclaw: "workspace:*"` in `devDependencies`, `peerDependencies` for IDE / typecheck
- `openclaw` block mirrors the IRC/Nostr shape; no `install.npmSpec` since this is a local bundled plugin

---

### 2. `extensions/pulseboard/openclaw.plugin.json`

```json
{
  "id": "pulseboard",
  "channels": ["pulseboard"],
  "configSchema": {
    "type": "object",
    "additionalProperties": false,
    "properties": {}
  }
}
```

Matches IRC and Nostr (empty `configSchema` is the standard minimal shape for bundled plugins).

---

### 3. `extensions/pulseboard/src/types.ts`

```typescript
export interface PulseBoardAccount {
  boardUrl: string;
  apiToken: string;
  username: string;
}

export interface PulseBoardConfig {
  accounts: Record<string, PulseBoardAccount>;
}

export interface PulseBoardMessage {
  id: string;
  boardId: string;
  authorId: string;
  content: string;
  timestamp: number;
}
```

No SDK imports needed here — purely local domain types.

---

### 4. `extensions/pulseboard/src/runtime.ts`

```typescript
import { createPluginRuntimeStore } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/runtime-store";
import type { PluginRuntime } from "openclaw/plugin-sdk/runtime-store";

const { setRuntime: setPulseBoardRuntime, getRuntime: getPulseBoardRuntime } =
  createPluginRuntimeStore<PluginRuntime>("PulseBoard runtime not initialized");

export { getPulseBoardRuntime, setPulseBoardRuntime };
```

Key points:
- Follows the Nostr pattern (simpler than IRC which also exports `clearRuntime`)
- `PluginRuntime` is re-exported from `openclaw/plugin-sdk/runtime-store` — no need to import from core
- Error message exactly matches the task spec: `"PulseBoard runtime not initialized"`

